<UserControl x:Class="GT3e.Tools.Views.VerificationTest"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:GT3e.Tools.ViewModels"
             mc:Ignorable="d"
             d:DesignHeight="450"
             d:DesignWidth="800"
             d:DataContext="{x:Type vm:VerificationTestViewModel}"
             MaxWidth="800"
             VerticalAlignment="Stretch"
             HorizontalAlignment="Stretch">
    <Grid HorizontalAlignment="Center"
          VerticalAlignment="Top">
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto" />
            <ColumnDefinition Width="*" />
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>

        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.ColumnSpan="2"
               Grid.Row="0">
            Verification Test
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="0"
                   Grid.ColumnSpan="2"
                   Grid.Row="1"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap">
            Before you can race with us at GT3e.com you need to complete a verification test and submit it for review.
            We will help you with this by monitoring ACC, detecting the session and automatically submitting it for
            review.  We will then monitor our backend system and detect when the session has been reviewed and update
            you on the status here.
        </TextBlock>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="0"
                   Grid.ColumnSpan="2"
                   Grid.Row="2"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap">
            You must complete a Single Player/ Quick Race session with the following settings at Zolder in
            any GT3
            car.  You must race cleanly and safely working your way up the field as far as you can.  Your result and
            lap times are
            important as they will be used to determine where you start your GT3e career, but of most
            importance is how you race.  At GT3e.com we only want to race against clean, fair and safe drivers so drive
            good lines, keep it on the black stuff and use good race tactics to pass your competitors cleanly without
            contact.
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="3">
            Day/Night Time
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="3"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            15:00
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="4"
               VerticalAlignment="Center">
            RaceSession Length
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="4"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            30 Minutes
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="5"
               VerticalAlignment="Center">
            Time Multiplier
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="5"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            x1
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="6"
               VerticalAlignment="Center">
            Starting Position
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="6"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            25
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="7">
            Opponent Count
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="7"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            24
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="8">
            Opponent Skill
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="8"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            90
        </TextBlock>

        <Label Grid.Column="0"
               Grid.Row="9">
            Opponent Agressiveness
        </Label>
        <TextBlock Grid.Column="1"
                   Grid.Row="9"
                   VerticalAlignment="Center">
            90
        </TextBlock>
        <TextBlock Grid.Row="10"
                   Grid.ColumnSpan="2"
                   Grid.Column="0">
            When you are ready to start you verification test, enter your Steam ID below and click Start. We will start
            monitoring ACC. When
            you have finished the race be sure to go into the Replay and save it.  We will validate the session and
            automatically upload files for verification using your Steam Id as your GT3e identity.
        </TextBlock>
        <StackPanel Grid.Column="1"
                    Grid.Row="11"
                    Orientation="Horizontal"
                    HorizontalAlignment="Right">
            <Label>Steam ID</Label>
            <TextBox Text="{Binding SteamId, Mode=TwoWay}"
                     Width="150"
                     Margin="1,1,10,1" />
            <Button Padding="5"
                    Command="{Binding StartCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsStartEnabled}"
                    Margin="1,1,10,1">
                Start
            </Button>
            <Button Padding="5"
                    Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsCancelEnabled}">
                Cancel
            </Button>
        </StackPanel>

    </Grid>

</UserControl>